The paper proposes the use of error-control codes and decoding algorithms to design crowdsourcing systems for reliable classification despite unreliable crowd workers. This suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed scheme with different crowdsourcing models, indicating a focus on data science (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
